#MEM id=upscaling-pipeline source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/pixel/skills/custom/upscaling-pipeline/SKILL.md
M|upscaling-pipeline|name: upscaling-pl
M|upscaling-pipeline|description: Image and video upscaling for YVON prd. Covers tool selection, scale factors, quality thresholds, batch ordering (upscale while next batch generates), and when to reject post-upscale.
M|upscaling-pipeline|version: 1.0.0
M|upscaling-pipeline|Upscaling is not optional polish — it is a required prd stage before delivery. AI-generated images at base resolution are rarely platform-ready. This skill makes upscaling systematic: right tool, righ
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Base resolution | Target platform | Scale factor | Output |
M|upscaling-pipeline||----------------|----------------|-------------|--------|
M|upscaling-pipeline|| 512×512 | Any | 4× | 2048×2048 |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| 768×768 | Instagram Feed | 2× | 1536×1536 (crop to 1080×1080) |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| 1024×1024 | Instagram Feed | 2× | 2048×2048 (crop to 1080×1080) |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| 1024×1280 | Instagram 4:5 | 2× | 2048×2560 (crop to 1080×1350) |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| 512×912 | Stories / Reels | 4× | 2048×3648 (crop to 1080×1920) |
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Rule:** Always upscale to at least 2× the final delivery resolution before cropping. Never upscale directly to exact delivery dimensions — leave headroom for crop adjustments.
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Tool | Best for | Avoid when |
M|upscaling-pipeline||------|----------|-----------|
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Real-ESRGAN (4× General) | Photorealistic images, lifestyle, editorial | Flat design or illustration |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Real-ESRGAN (4× Anime) | Illustration, graphic style | Realistic photography |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Topaz Gigapixel AI | Maximum quality, final hero images | Quick batch runs (slow) |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Stable Diffusion img2img (upscale) | Adding detail at upscale stage | When prompt fidelity must be preserved exactly |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Lanczos (software) | Emergency / no tool available | Never for hero images |
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Default for YVON prd:** Real-ESRGAN 4× General for Novizio lifestyle/editorial. Real-ESRGAN 4× General for Hourbour people-with-devices.
M|upscaling-pipeline|Run these checks after upscaling before formatting:
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Check | Pass | Fail → Action |
M|upscaling-pipeline||-------|------|--------------|
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Detail integrity | Fine details (fabric texture, hair, UI elements) are sharper, not smeared | Re-upscale with different tool |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| No hallucinated detail | Upscaler has not invented new elements not in original | Reject — return to generation |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| No over-sharpening | Edges look natural, no halo artefacts | Reduce sharpening setting, re-run |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Face quality | Face detail is improved, not degraded | Run face-enhance pass separately |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Text clarity | Any intentional text is more legible, not distorted | Run text-focused upscale or reject |
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Rule:** If an image passes QC before upscaling but fails post-upscale, do not deliver the pre-upscale version. Fix the upscaling. The base image passes; only the upscale technique failed.
M|upscaling-pipeline|Video upscaling is slower and riskier than image upscaling. Approach with more caution.
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Condition | Action |
M|upscaling-pipeline||-----------|--------|
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Output is < 1080p and platform requires 1080p | Upscale required |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Output is 1080p and platform requires 1080p | No upscale needed |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Output has visible compression artifacts | Re-gen at higher quality setting instead of upscaling |
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Rule:** Re-generation beats upscaling for video quality issues. Only upscale when re-generation is not feasible (budget, time).
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Tool | Use case |
M|upscaling-pipeline||------|---------|
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Topaz Video AI | Primary tool — frame interpolation + upscale |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Real-ESRGAN (video mode) | Faster, lower quality than Topaz |
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Default settings (Topaz Video AI):**
M|upscaling-pipeline|- Model: Proteus (for realistic cnt) / Iris (for faces)
M|upscaling-pipeline|- Enhancement: 2× scale
M|upscaling-pipeline|- Frame rate: match original (do not change frame rate at upscale stage)
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Check | Pass | Fail |
M|upscaling-pipeline||-------|------|------|
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Motion smoothness | Motion unchanged or improved | Motion blur or ghosting introduced |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Face stability | Face detail improved | Face flickering or morphing introduced by upscaler |
M|upscaling-pipeline|| Edge detail | Subject edges sharper | Halo or ringing around edges |
M|upscaling-pipeline|Pixel runs overlapping stages to maximize throughput:
M|upscaling-pipeline|```
M|upscaling-pipeline|[Batch A: gen] → [Batch A: QC] → [Batch A: Upscale] → [Batch A: Format] → [Deliver]
M|upscaling-pipeline|↓
M|upscaling-pipeline|[Batch B: gen] → [Batch B: QC] → [Batch B: Upscale] → ...
M|upscaling-pipeline|```
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Rule:** Start Batch B generation while Batch A is upscaling. Never wait for full delivery of Batch A before starting Batch B. The bottleneck is upscaling (slowest stage) — parallel staging keeps the
M|upscaling-pipeline|**Exception:** Do not start Batch B if Batch A's QC pass rate is < 60%. Investigate prompt before spending more generation budget.
M|upscaling-pipeline|After every upscaling run, append to mem.md:
M|upscaling-pipeline|```
M|upscaling-pipeline|[date] — [vtr] — [cg] — [tool used] — [scale factor] — [pass rate post-upscale] — [notes]
M|upscaling-pipeline|```
M|upscaling-pipeline|If a tool consistently degrades a specific type of image (e.g., Real-ESRGAN smearing fabric texture), log it and update the tool selection guide in this skill.